# CloveJS WebSocket example — HTTP requests
#
# A dependency-free alternative to a Postman/Insomnia collection: this plain
# text format is read natively by JetBrains IDEs (Run > HTTP Client) and by
# VS Code's "REST Client" extension (humao.rest-client).
#
# The WEBSOCKET blocks at the bottom are JetBrains-only (WebStorm/IntelliJ
# 2023.2+). VS Code's REST Client extension has no WebSocket support — use
# `npx wscat -c ws://localhost:3000/ws/echo` there instead.
#
# Start the server first: npm run dev -w clovejs-example-websocket

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
@wsUrl = ws://localhost:3000

### Room state over HTTP — empty until someone connects
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/rooms/lobby

### Push a message into the room from HTTP. Every socket connected to
### /ws/chat/lobby receives it — open the WEBSOCKET block below first.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/rooms/lobby
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "from": "ops",
  "text": "Deploy finished"
}

### Room state again — the message is in `recent` now
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/rooms/lobby

### Echo socket — whatever you send comes straight back
WEBSOCKET {{wsUrl}}/ws/echo

Hello over WebSocket
===
wait-for-server
Sent after the echo comes back

### Chat room — a parameterised socket route. Open this in one tab, then run
### the POST above, or open it a second time as a different user to watch the
### two sockets see each other.
WEBSOCKET {{wsUrl}}/ws/chat/lobby?as=ada

Hello everyone
